cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on enhancing text comprehension and inference through semantic role labeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep learning models, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves improving embeddings for more fine-grained semantics, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on machine reading comprehension and inference datasets, which could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
